The paper discusses the use of deep learning and reinforcement learning for mobile robotics, specifically in the context of autonomous driving and navigation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of simulators and evaluation in simulation, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the need for better benchmarks and mechanisms to bridge the gap between simulation and reality, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
